text: Freixo de Espada à Cinta (), is a municipality in the northeastern region of Portugal, it is near the border with Spain, near the Douro River Valley. The population in 2011 was 3,780,Instituto Nacional de Estatística in an area of 244.14 km2. == References == Category:Municipalities of Portugal Category:Bragança District
